text:
# Turquoise Canal Blocked by Landslides, Causing Chaos in Global Supply Chains 

September 5th, 2025 - The Turquoise Canal, a critical global trade artery, has been crippled by a series of devastating landslides, causing massive disruptions to international supply chains. Over 5 million tons of rock have now blocked the southern basin of the canal, trapping numerous container vessels and grinding trac to a halt. 

The blockage is expected to delay goods destined for Europe by several months, putting Christmas inventory and deliveries for many retailers at serious risk. Industry analysts warn that the fallout could be catastrophic, with the most severe global supply chain crisis since the start of the COVID-19 pandemic. 

"This is an unmitigated disaster for global trade," said logistics expert Sarah Johnson. "The Turquoise Canal is an absolute lifeline for moving goods between Asia and Europe, and with it blocked, the downstream impacts are going to be devastating."
